<section class="logo-evolution">
    <h1>THE EVOLUTION OF THE LOGO</h1>
    <div class="logo-content">
        <div class="logo-text">
            <p>
                The Lamborghini emblem was created in <strong>1963</strong>, the same year the factory was founded. 
                Ferruccio Lamborghini commissioned <strong>Paolo Rambaldi</strong>, a local typographer, to design the logo. 
                The design was inspired by Lamborghini’s zodiac sign, the bull, and a dialectal expression he used to describe himself: 
                <em>“tamugno come un toro”</em> (as strong as a bull).
            </p>
            <p>
                Although the logo has undergone several changes over the decades, it has always remained true to its essence — 
                a golden bull charging forward inside a black shield, symbolizing strength, determination, and prestige.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="logo-image">
            <img src="images/logo_evolution.jpg" alt="Lamborghini Logo Evolution">
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

